Tokenomics

3% Holders Reward

Every transaction automatically contributes to Holders wallet. This means long term is a key factor, as their balance of BlackLivesMatter grow indefinitely through Holding.

5% Charity Donation

Sent directly to the charity wallet. To then be used for donations to various charity organizations such as

Black Lives Matter Foundation. Go Fund Me Projects.
2% Auto Burn

Every transaction automatically contributes to Burn liquidity. This contributes to less volatility and a continuously increasing price floor.

Our Roadmap

March 13:

Breonna Taylor was murdered in Louisville, Kentucky by three police officers during a no-knock search. Taylor was 26.

May 25:

George Floyd was murdered by a police officer in Minneapolis, Minnesota after being arrested and pinned to the ground. Floyd was 46.

May 27:

Protests spread across the country and major roads are blocked off by protesters. First protests take place in Chicago and Louisville.

June 3:

Three other officers involved in Floyd killing charged aiding in murder. Chauvin charges increased to second-degree murder.

Start of BLACKLIVESMATTER foundation

Rather than having a third party charity doing the charity, our community and team volunteers will be out and about doing the hard work and donating to charities and places chosen by the community, this will all be live and on video for the holders to see

How To Buy

BNB METHOD

Download TrustWallet

PancakeSwap LINK:

Buy Now
1. Download TrustWallet (an app for your phone).
2. Purchase BNB
If you already have BNB or BSC, just transfer them to your TrustWallet Address.

Swap BNB to BSC

3. Click on BNB > Click on "..." (more) > Swap to Smart Chain > Send
VIDEO EXAMPLE: VIEW

Go to DApps

4. Go to the DApps tab at the bottom, and find PancakeSwap. Click.
iPhone users may need to enable the trust browser, Open Safari type: "trust://browser_enable"
You can also click the BUY NOW button on our website if you're not on mobile.

Select Currency

5. Click "Select a currency" and enter this contract address into the search field, and you should be able to find BLACKLIVESMATTER.
0xf3afed6a2530dae653a08f96231aed7e18c183dc
6. Before swapping, click on the cog wheel and set the slippage to between 11-12%.

Buy BLACKLIVESMATTER and HODL

7. Swap BNB for "BLACKLIVESMATTER".
8. Open TrustWallet, on the Top Right icon, search BLACKLIVESMATTER, Toggle it. View them in your wallet. Lastly...
HODL!

    The Beginning:

    Our work began in 2018 with promoting the official blacklivesmatter.com movement, in my free time i started helping my neighborhoods give more attention to this great cause, giving people more awareness of what was happening in our culture, i started to get more and more listeners of my words and organize bigger groups, then started asking for donation for blacklivesmatter.com



    I grew up in a middle class family, i don’t consider myself privileged as i always had school racism, always had problems with my skin color, i was different, in America it really hits hard if you have a different color of the skin, you are not in their group, you will never get treated right, you will always be emancipated, ALWAYS. I want this to be stopped, I Am Tired, We are Tired seeing people like:

    The Tragic Deaths

    Eric Garner, died after he was wrestled to the ground by a New York police officer on suspicion of illegally selling cigarettes.

    or

    Tamir Rice, a boy of 12, was shot dead in Cleveland, Ohio by a police officer after reports of a male who was "probably a juvenile" pointing a gun that was "probably fake" at passers by.

    or even

    Stephon Clark died after being shot at least seven times in his grandmother's backyard in Sacramento, California, by police who were investigating a nearby break-in. Only a mobile phone was found at the scene, and Mr Clark was unarmed. The release of a police video of the incident sparked major protests in the city.

    and..

    Breonna Taylor, a 26-year-old emergency medical technician, was shot eight times when officers raided her apartment in Louisville, Kentucky. Louisville police said they returned fire after one officer was shot at and wounded. Breonna Taylor's family filed a lawsuit, and in September 2020 reached a settlement of $12m (£9.4m) with the city authorities.

    With protests we thought that police violence would have stopped But:



    George Floyd died after being arrested in Minneapolis and held down by police officers, one of whom had his knee on Mr Floyd's neck for more than nine minutes. He pleaded that he couldn't breathe, and after his death, protests broke out across the US, and there were demonstrations in other parts of the world.

    Finally the world saw what was happening, I was hoping that no more black people were killed as this problem gained more attention, the police would stop doing that..

    Unfortunately Daunte Wright was shot and killed in Brooklyn Center, just north of Minneapolis. After being pulled over for a traffic violation, the police told Mr Wright he was being arrested for an outstanding warrant.


    Here you can see what a year was 2020 for the blacklivesmatter.com movement, what we’ve done and who we helped: https://blacklivesmatter.com/2020-impact-report/

    We need your help with this project: A poll in June 2016 found that 65% of black American adults supported Black Lives Matter and 40% of white American adults support it. Fifty-nine percent of black Americans thought that Black Lives Matter would "be effective, in the long run, in helping blacks achieve equality" and 34% of white Americans thought so. A 2017 Harvard-Harris survey found that 35% of whites and 83% of blacks have a favorable view of the movement. According to an analysis by The Guardian of statistics collected by the US Crisis Monitor, during most of 2020 "US law enforcement agencies have used teargas, pepper spray, rubber bullets, and beatings at a much higher percentage at Black Lives Matter demonstrations than at pro-Trump or other rightwing protests", regardless of whether the protest was violent or peaceful. The analysis also notes that "the vast majority of the thousands of protests across the United States in the past year have been peaceful.
